right-click-file (1.1.0) stable; urgency=low

  * apt hook: automatically re-apply the DING patch after a DING update.
  * apt hook: notify logged-in GNOME users on patch re-application or failure.
  * apt hook: store timestamped backups in a dedicated subdirectory.
  * postinst: save a read-only original backup of desktopManager.js before patching.
  * postinst: detect and clean residual patch before saving original backup.
  * postinst: install apt hook configuration to /etc/apt/apt.conf.d/.
  * postinst: store SHA256 hash of desktopManager.js for change detection.
  * prerm: restore desktopManager.js from original backup as first priority.
  * prerm: fall back to patch-ding.py remove if original backup is missing.
  * prerm: fall back to GitLab download as last resort, version-aware.
  * prerm: remove apt hook before any file operation to avoid race conditions.

